England reached 341 for five on day one of the first Test against West Indies in Antigua . 
  Ian Bell and Joe Root put on 177 runs for the fourth wicket . 
  Ben Stokes was unbeaten on 71 at the end of the day . 
  England's top three are very one-paced and it was a problem on the first morning of the Test . 
  Jonathan Trott was dismissed for a duck on his return to the side . 
  Alastair Cook was out for 11 on the opening day of the match . 
 